<h1>Getting there</h1>
<p>Because of COVID-19, people in Korea are reluctant to travel outside of the country this summer, as they would have to return to a mandatory 14-day quarantine. So Koreans are packing every flight to Jeju. A friend told me all the golf courses are pretty much booked for the rest of the golf season. So good luck getting a tee time if you are looking to play a round there. I didn't see an empty seat on the Jeju Airlines flight from Gimpo International Airport or the t'way Airlines flight we took back to Seoul. We stayed at a modest little hotel on the southwest end of the island, just a few steps away from beautiful <a href="https://goo.gl/maps/KXkYsF8nqmVsAAHG6" target="_blank">Cheonjeyeon Waterfall</a> and rented a little Hyundai Avante to traverse the palm-tree filled island. (Note: My wife did all the research and is a notorious online deals hoarder, so despite the high demand, it is possible to find decent prices for flights, hotel, and car rental. Fortunately for us, we visited Jeju just before the big "2nd Wave of COVID-19," otherwise we would have had to cancel our trip.)</p>

